<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> How to get Shelob to Work<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.64)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=17333'>Philly "KingChoke" Kemp</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=17333&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 24, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> I just recently traded for 4x Shelbo, EoL. People traded them so easily because it <br />
was no fun playing her now with all the annoying possession removal. Since <br />
Shelob, Eater of Light revolves on minions being stacked on Web, which is a <br />
possession, you have to keep those possessions safe. Each Web that is discarded <br />
means that shelob is now a –9 strength. Each Web discarded means Shelob loses a possible 9 strength. Once your opponent kills all of your webs, your Shelob is just an old 8 strength. With all the big drawves, elves, and men being so strong, they could easily kill off Shelob, or at least win her regular and fierce skirmishes. Since Shelob decks are usually based on Shelob herself, your deck would be messed up once your opponent discarded your Webs. I tell you another thing. You may think that most people DON’T play possession removal but I tell you, THEY DO. With Mount Doom bringing out “Queen of Deck Screwer” (Galadriel, Lady Redeemed), it is know even harder to play Shelob. In this article a will talk about a few ways to help here work better against decks that play Galariel, Lady Redeemed and Mr. Possession removal (Derufin).<br />
<br />
First of all, ways to help win going against Derufin. Here is Derufin’s text.<br />
<br />
Regroup: While you have exactly 5 cards in hand, you may exert Derufin to discard an engine, machine, or possession.<br />
<br />
Here are a few ways to counter this guy.<br />
<br />
Tower Lieutenant:<br />
This is probably one of the easiest ways to counter Derufin. Since your opponent needs exactly 5 cards to use Derufin’s text, what happens when you get rid of cards in your opponents hand?????!!!!! Oh yea! Most of the time your opponent rigs every thing so that in the regroup phase he’ll have only 5 cards. Since this is the case, Tower Lieutenant can help. It says each time he wins a skirmish, you opponent must discard 2 cards at random from hand. This is really good to get rid of cards in your opponents hand. Plus, this guy is a 10 strength, 3 vitality minion. He is also only an uncommon. On top of that, he is an ORC. This also helps you to pump shelob. Frodo, CH would hurt this strategy but he is not that common any more.<br />
<br />
Orc Inquisitor: <br />
The same as Tower Lieutenant. Discards card from opponents hand. <br />
<br />
Tower of Baradur:<br />
Playing 4 of these is tech against Derufin. If you had four out, every time your<br />
opponent moved (even in the Fellowship phase), he would have to discard 4 <br />
cards from hand. Chances are good that he would only have no more that 8 cards <br />
tops begin with. This means that if he didn’t play anything, he still would only have 4 cards. I don’t think that enough to use Derufin’s text, is it?<br />
<br />
And finally just plain old cards that could kill derufin in battle (like mixing Gollum in and playing YaLaaT), or cards that could kill him period (like hate), or using stuff to discard stuff from his hand.<br />
<br />
Galadriel, Lady Redeemed:<br />
<br />
Terrible as the Don:<br />
This is the most popular card to kill Galareil, LR. This card can wound her three times (which would kill her). There is a way for the freeps to counter this, however. This is that when you play this, they can discard to elves to prevent that. How hard would that be to do? Pretty hard, huh. <br />
<br />
Hate:<br />
This is a good card to kill her, however it is not the best way to kill her. You could play 3 of theses at a time to kill her, but this would be very hard to execute.<br />
<br />
Sorry for not posting mush on ways to cope with Galadreil but that is all I can think of for right now. If you have any ways, your welcome to tell me.<br />
<br />
Here is a shadow that could counter the Mr. and Mrs. a little.<br />
<br />
Shelob, EoL x4<br />
Gollum, OV x2<br />
Gollum, MT x1<br />
Tower Lieutenant x3<br />
Orc Inquisitor x4<br />
Isengard Retainer x4<br />
Isengard Servant x4<br />
Isengard Shawmen x2<br />
Tower of Baradur x4<br />
Web x4<br />
Terrible as the Don x2<br />
<br />
Hope this encourages you a little to not give up on shelob. It’s about time that Shadows rise.<br />
